    .text-h1(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="50") Personal Data Processing Policy
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="60") 1. General Provisions
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="70") This personal data processing policy has been compiled in accordance with the requirements of Federal Law No. 152-FZ of July 27, 2006, "On Personal Data" and defines the procedure for processing personal data and measures to ensure the security of personal data taken by Verba Clinic LLC (hereinafter referred to as the Operator).
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="80") 1.1 The Operator sets as its most important goal and condition for carrying out its activities the observance of human and civil rights and freedoms when processing their personal data, including the protection of the rights to privacy, personal and family secrets.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="90") 1.2 This Operator policy regarding the processing of personal data (hereinafter referred to as the Policy) applies to all information that the Operator may receive about visitors to the website <a href='domnadom.surge.sh'>domnadom.surge.sh</a>.
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="110") 2. Basic concepts used in the Policy
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="120") 2.1 Automated processing of personal data – processing of personal data using computer technology;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="130") 2.2 Blocking of personal data – temporary cessation of processing of personal data (except in cases where processing is necessary to clarify personal data);
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="140") 2.3 Website – a collection of graphic and informational materials, as well as computer programs and databases, ensuring their availability on the Internet at the network address <a href='domnadom.surge.sh'>domnadom.surge.sh</a>;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="150") 2.4 Personal data information system — a set of personal data contained in databases and the information technologies and technical means that ensure their processing;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="160") 2.5 Depersonalization of personal data — actions that make it impossible to determine, without the use of additional information, the attribution of personal data to a specific User or another personal data subject;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="170") 2.6 Processing of personal data — any action (operation) or set of actions (operations) performed with or without the use of automation tools with personal data, including collection, recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, clarification (updating, modification), retrieval, use, transfer (distribution, provision, access), depersonalization, blocking, deletion, and destruction of personal data;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="180") 2.7 Operator – a government agency, municipal authority, legal entity, or individual that, independently or jointly with other persons, organizes and/or carries out the processing of personal data, and determines the purposes of processing personal data, the composition of personal data to be processed, and the actions (operations) performed with personal data;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="190") 2.8 Personal data – any information relating directly or indirectly to a specific or identifiable User of the website <a href='domnadom.surge.sh'>domnadom.surge.sh</a>;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 2.9 User – any visitor to the website <a href='domnadom.surge.sh'>domnadom.surge.sh</a>;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 2.10 Provision of personal data – actions aimed at disclosing personal data to a specific person or a specific group of persons;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 2.11 Dissemination of personal data – any actions aimed at disclosing personal data to an indefinite number of persons (transfer of personal data) or making personal data available to an indefinite number of persons, including disclosing personal data in the media, posting it on information and telecommunications networks, or providing access to personal data in any other way;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 2.12 Cross-border transfer of personal data – transfer of personal data to the territory of a foreign state to a foreign government agency, a foreign individual, or a foreign legal entity;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 2.13 Destruction of personal data – any actions resulting in the irreversible destruction of personal data, making it impossible to further restore the contents of personal data in the personal data information system and/or the destruction of tangible media containing personal data.
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 3. The Operator may process the following personal data of the User
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 3.1 Last name, first name, patronymic;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 3.2 Email address;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 3.3 Phone numbers;
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 3.4 The site also collects and processes anonymized data about visitors (including cookies) using internet statistics services (Yandex Metrica, Google Analytics, and others).
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 3.5 The above data is hereinafter collectively referred to as Personal Data.
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 4. Purposes of Personal Data Processing
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 4.1 The purpose of processing the User's personal data is to inform the User via email; to provide the User with access to services, information, and/or materials contained on the website.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 4.2 The Operator also has the right to send the User notifications about new products and services, special offers, and various events. The User can always opt out of receiving informational messages by sending an email to the Operator at privacy@domnadom.surge.sh with the subject line "Opt-out of notifications about new products and services and special offers." p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 4.3 Anonymized User data collected through internet statistics services is used to collect information about User actions on the website and improve the quality of the website and its content.
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 5. Legal basis for personal data processing
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 5.1 The Operator processes the User's personal data only if it is completed and/or submitted by the User independently through special forms located on the website <a href='domnadom.surge.sh'>domnadom.surge.sh</a>. By completing the relevant forms and/or submitting their personal data to the Operator, the User expresses their consent to this Policy.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 5.2 The Operator processes anonymized data about the User if this is permitted in the User's browser settings (saving cookies and using JavaScript technology are enabled).
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") Procedure for the Collection, Storage, Transfer, and Other Processing of Personal Data
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 6. The security of personal data processed by the Operator is ensured through the implementation of legal, organizational, and technical measures necessary to fully comply with the requirements of current legislation in the field of personal data protection.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 6.1 The Operator ensures the security of personal data and takes all possible measures to prevent unauthorized persons from accessing personal data.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 6.2 The User's personal data will never, under any circumstances, be transferred to third parties, except in cases related to compliance with current legislation.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 6.3 If any inaccuracies in personal data are discovered, the User may update them independently by sending a notification to the Operator's email address privacy@domnadom.surge.sh with the subject line "Update personal data."
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 6.4 The processing period for personal data is unlimited. The User may revoke their consent to the processing of personal data at any time by sending a notification to the Operator via email to the Operator's email address privacy@domnadom.surge.sh with the subject line "Withdrawal of consent to the processing of personal data."
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 7. Cross-border transfer of personal data
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 7.1 Before commencing the cross-border transfer of personal data, the operator is obliged to ensure that the foreign state to which the personal data is to be transferred ensures reliable protection of the rights of personal data subjects.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 7.2 The cross-border transfer of personal data to the territory of foreign states that do not meet the above requirements may only be carried out with the personal data subject's written consent to the cross-border transfer of their personal data and/or the execution of an agreement to which the personal data subject is a party.
    .text-xl(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 8. Final Provisions
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 8.1 The User may obtain any clarification on any questions regarding the processing of their personal data by contacting the Operator via email at privacy@domnadom.surge.sh.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 8.2 This document will reflect any changes to the Operator's personal data processing policy. This policy is valid indefinitely until replaced by a new version.
    p.text-m(data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100") 8.3 The current version of the Policy is freely available on the Internet at <a>https: href='domnadom.surge.sh<'domnadom.surge.sh</a>a-konfidentsialnosti.